    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Revision of Muhlenbergia (Poaceae, Chloridoideae, Cynodonteae, Muhlenbergiinae) in Peru: classification, phylogeny, and a new species, M. romaschenkoi" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure4>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure1> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. A-C Muhlenbergia caxamarcensis Laegaard & Sanchez Vega A habit B panicle branch C floret D-G Muhlenbergia ciliata (Kunth) Trin D habit E ligule F glumes G floret. Drawings A-C from Laegaard and Sanchez Vega (1990) from holotype collection (S. A. Renvoize & S. Laegaard 4962) D-G from Peterson and Annable (1991) drawn from P. M. Peterson & C. R. Annable 4541 (WS)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/254045" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. A, B Maximum-likelihood tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in red occur in South America; scale bar = 2 %." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/254042" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

